{"key":"processedPost-9103835","value":{"id":9103835,"first":6789654,"last":9106781,"when":1224524509,"utime":"10/20/08 08:41 PM","cleanedPost":"Potting soils were commonly used as casing material ten to twenty years ago.&nbsp; However, peat-verm is and always has been superior to potting soils.<br />In addition, casing mix and bulk substrates should be <i>pasteurized</i>, not sterilized.&nbsp; <i>Pasteurization involves heating pre-moistened, field capacity material to 140F to 160F (60c to 70c) for one hour.</i>&nbsp; Super-heating in the microwave is partial sterilization, which makes it more prone to contaminants, not less.<br />RR"}}